{
  "text": "3 This is consistent with a result about efficient depreciation in forward looking cost models derived in [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . These authors find that when the charges set on the basis of such a model are periodically redetermined, the efficient path of charges depends on the expected path of costs over time. Specifically, if costs are expected to rise (fall) in real terms, then initial charges should be below (above) the levelized (that is, smoothed) charge, assuming that the regulatory commitment to the resulting price path is credible.",
  "citation_candidates": [
